{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"fields":{"description":"Own the **remediation-mode GATE**: the freshness-window + precondition check that decides\nwhether a re-review runs in floored (remediation) mode or as a normal full review, and wire\nit parallel to `drift_refresh` in `_run_plan_review`. (This is the task-4 candidate-check; the\nPass-3 drop math it gates is task cc5b. Body/title were previously swapped with task 3689 —\nthis restores the epic's 6-task decomposition.)\n\n## Preconditions (ALL required, else byte-identical full review)\n\n- config enabled (`remediation_mode` key; see rollout note below)\n- plan changed since the prior review\n- **code UNCHANGED since baseline** — detected deterministically by comparing the gate's\n  attested `verified_at_sha` (the origin/main snapshot SHA the gate signs into the prior\n  review's manifest) against the current run's `verified_at_sha`. Equal ⇒ code unchanged;\n  differ ⇒ code drifted. This reuses the already-signed snapshot ref — no new diff machinery.\n- registry unchanged (criteria-routing material fingerprint equal to the prior review's)\n- a prior `REVIEW_RESULT` sidecar WITH finding text is available (task e344)\n- the last review of ANY kind (full or partial) is within the window (default 60 min),\n  measured from that last review and **reset on each review** so the loop persists across a\n  series of edits and lapses to a normal full review only after the agent goes idle.\n\nCode-changed / both-drifted → full review (`drift_refresh` path byte-unchanged, out of scope).\n\n## Rollout (resolves the default-on advisory)\n\nThe `remediation_mode` config key ships **default-OFF** for one release (expand-contract:\nship off → validate on the dogfood corpus → flip the default on in a follow-up), so existing\nconsumers do not silently get a narrowed verdict on upgrade. Setting the key off (or absent)\nrestores byte-identical full-review behavior at any time — the back-out.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Candidate check enforces ALL preconditions; any failure → full review (`src/rebar/llm/plan_review/__init__.py`, `attest.py`)\n- [ ] `remediation_mode` config key (default-OFF for v1) + window minutes (default 60) in `src/rebar/config.py`; key off/absent → byte-identical full review\n- [ ] \"code unchanged\" is the `verified_at_sha` equality check (prior manifest vs current run); registry-unchanged is the routing material-fingerprint equality check\n- [ ] Window measured from the last review of any kind, reset on each review\n- [ ] both-drifted → full review; `drift_refresh` path byte-unchanged\n- [ ] Wiring is parallel to `drift_refresh` in `_run_plan_review`; the Pass-3 drop math itself lives in cc5b (this task only decides remediation-mode eligibility)","title":"Remediation-mode gate: freshness window + preconditions + wiring"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1782766152196065001,"uuid":"02596599-0d4e-4e1f-b7eb-27aaf930f7f5"}